import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_numeric(data['X'], errors='coerce')
    data['Y'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Y'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['X', 'Y'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['X'], data['Y'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between X and Y?')
    corr = data['X'].corr(data['Y'])
    ax.axvline(x=corr, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Correlation: {corr:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['X'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['X'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X-Y'] = data['X'] - data['Y']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X-Y', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['X-Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['X-Y'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['X-Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['X-Y'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of X-Y?')
    ax.set_xlabel('X-Y')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['X'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='X')
    plt.plot(data['X'], data['Y'])
    plt.title('What is the trend in X over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
